Real simple HTTP CLI client.

1 - You set parameters for your HTTP request. It is pretty personnalisable
2 - Launch script, get response.


Important features :
- Support SSL (still experimental, I guess)
- Basic and Digest authentification
- GET, POST and COOKIES parameters
- You can set additionnal headers. Beware malformed headers can fail the request.


Options :

-h <host>               Host : sub.mydomain.com
-p <port>               Defaut : 80
-s                      Enable HTTPS
-u <url>                Path : /folder/main
-m <method>             HTTP method : GET,POST,HEAD,etc
--creds <login:pass>
--useragent <user agent>        Credentials for basic HTTP auth

GET, POST and COOKIE data must be JSON encoded : {'p1':'v1','p2':'v2'}
--get <data get>                GET data
--post <data post>              POST data
--cookie <data cookie>          COOKIE data

--showreq       show request
--showbody      show body response
-v              enable verbose



